response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Proper Divisors\", \"description\": \"A proper divisor of an integer `n` is a positive integer that divides `n`, but not equal to `n`. Write a function `sum_of_proper_divisors` that calculates the sum of all proper divisors of a given number.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_proper_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of all proper divisors of the input number.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_proper_divisors(n: int) -> int:\\n    total = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            total += i\\n    return total\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_proper_divisors(28) == 28\", \"assert sum_of_proper_divisors(12) == 16\", \"assert sum_of_proper_divisors(15) == 1\", \"assert sum_of_proper_divisors(220) == 284\"] }"
